. a true love story, first time i came to islands brygge was in the mid 90's. it was one of my first visits to copenhagen and denmark as an adult. back then islands brygge was very different from the smart and chic area it is today. there were empty warehouses, old factory buildings and houses which needed to be renovated. cheap bodegas instead of today's coffeeshops and upscale restaurants. i was amazed that this was less than a 10 minutes walk from the main square of copenhagen. what a place! but i was in love with an amazing danish girl. and she had given me a choice. if i moved to copenhagen, she promised to be mine. so we stayed with some of her friends at their apartment at islands brygge. i was almost about to pack my bag and catch an earlier flight home. luckily i didn't. and the amazing girl kept her promise... an old memory that i came to think about, this freezing cold but beautiful morning! as i take pictures! i wish i would have had a camera with me back then... . . the waggon is a part of the cultural history of islands brygge (iceland harbour). . and thx for reading my story ğŸ˜‰. . . . islandsbrygge kÃ¸benhavn mycopenhagen magic sunset train sunrise photoshop endofanera photoartist photoart urbex darkparadise thebalddude denmark mitkÃ¸benhavn dawn light waggon nighttime copenhagen amazingplace uecph photoofthenight canon longexposure moody beautifuldestinations photooftheweek besttownintheworld

from fireboat to restaurant - part 1 - the christianshavner ferry is an former swedish passenger ferry approved in sweden for the carriage of 60 passengers provisionally until may 2019. the swedish state maritime museums consider the ship to be historically valuable. the ship was built in 1880 at ljusne mekaniska verksted to be set as stockholm's first fireboat. it became the world's most modern fireboat, capable of spraying 2,000 jets of water per minute. at first practice, the ship sprayed water on the roof of the grand hotel in stockholm. the fireboat was copied, both by the fire departments of new york and gothenburg. the ship's first name was s:t erik after the name of stockholm's patron saint. the fireboat was used until 1932, where it was sold for civilian use in gothenburg and converted to passenger traffic. restaurant christianshavn canal harbour copenhagen copenhagenfacades ibyen sharingcph delditkbh cphpicks govisitdenmark visitcopenhagen igerscopenhagen igersdenmark loves_united_denmark loves_denmark typicalscandinavia thebestofscandinavia restaurantchristianshavnerfÃ¦rgen ferry historical swedish fireboat ship bÃ¥d skib kÃ¸benhavn
